com.variant.client

Interface SessionAttributes


  • public interface SessionAttributes
    A map-like collection of session attributes, returned by Session.getAttributes(). Attribute names and values are arbitrary non-null strings. The state of this object reflects the shared state at the time of creation. All non-mutating methods are local and may not reflect the shared state. If there is a possibility that the shared state may have been updated since this object was created, you need to refresh from the shared state by getting a new copy of this object with Session.getAttributes(). Conversely, all mutating methods update the shared state on the server. By the time mutating methods return, this object is refreshed with the current shared state.
    Since:
    0.10
